      <akn:section eId="sec_19_1302_01">
        <akn:num>19-1302.01</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Role of court in administration of trust.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_19-1302_01_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The court may intervene in the administration of a trust to the extent its jurisdiction is invoked by an interested person or as provided by law.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_19-1302_01_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A trust is not subject to continuing judicial supervision unless ordered by the court.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_19-1302_01_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A judicial proceeding involving a trust may relate to any matter involving the trustâ€™s administration, including a request for instructions and an action to declare rights.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
